<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-18T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-18T20:00:00-05:00" n="111" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/6676</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Consular Officers in
                                        Latin American Countries</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-18T20:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 18, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Decline to certify invoices for persons or firms whose names are on
                                enemy trading list and for persons known to be acting as cloaks for
                                said listed firms except where it is alleged that shipment is
                                covered by license of War Trade Board. Sales of local branches of
                                firms in United States to firms on enemy trading list are not to be
                                objected to when alleged to have been duly licensed. All firms
                                suspected of misrepresentation should be promptly reported. Like
                                treatment should be accorded to firms alleging possession British or
                                French [or Italian<note n="1" xml:id="d111fn1">Added in accordance
                                    with circular telegram of March 9, 1918 (File No. 763.72112/6676
                                    Suppl.).</note>] license.</p>
                            <p>Notify all consular officials.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>